{\b\f0{\cf2\scaps Programmer's Guide}\line\fs32 About this guide}\par\pard\sb100

This document is intended to describe the libraries of routines
 and objects available in the MythOS\'99 collection of software for
 Windows 95/98/NT.  MythOS is intended to provide a robust set of
 tools for the rapid development of high-performance,
 high-quality entertainment/multi-media software on the PC.  This
 manual assumes knowledge of C, C++, and some x86 Assembly as
 well as basic knowledge of Windows 32-bit application
 programming and the Win32 API.
\par

\line{\b\fs28 Organization}\par

This guide is divided into the following sections:
\par

{\uldb Overview}{\v PG_OVERVIEW} of MythOS -- Contains the introduction
 to the guide, the components available, and the intended uses of the
 libraries in the MythOS collection.
\par

{\i\uldb System}{\v PG_SYSTEM_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the MythOS
 system and library management class.
\par

{\i\uldb Ivory}{\v PG_IVORY_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the Charybdis
 memory-management system.
\par

{\i\uldb XFile}{\v PG_XFILE_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the Charybdis file
 system.
\par

{\i\uldb Chronos}{\v PG_CHRONOS_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the Charybdis timer
 system.
\par

{\i\uldb Bozo}{\v PG_BOZO_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the multi-threading kernel
 library.
\par

{\i\uldb Max}{\v PG_MAX_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the arbitrary event
 processing system.
\par

{\i\uldb Felix}{\v PG_FELIX_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the fixed-point
 support library.
\par

{\i\uldb Van Gogh}{\v PG_VNGO_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the 2D graphics
 output library.
\par

{\i\uldb Escher}{\v PG_ESCH_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the 3D graphics
 library
\par

{\i\uldb Gutenberg}{\v PG_GBERG_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the font system.
\par

{\i\uldb Turner}{\v PG_TURNER_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the network interface.
\par

{\i\uldb Newton}{\v PG_NEWTON_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the physics system.
\par

{\i\uldb Bach}{\v PG_BACH_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the sound system.
\par

{\i\uldb Spielberg}{\v PG_SBERG_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the animation/movie player.
\par

{\i\uldb Pane}{\v PG_PANE_OVERVIEW} -- Describes the GUI helper library.
